parameters.name: CycleTimeZone
parameters.description:
The time zone.

Reference Format: "+08:00"

Valid Range: "-12:59" to "+13:00"

parameters.name: CycleType
parameters.description:
Determines the time period over which data is aggregated. If no aggregation dimension is specified, the query defaults to providing detailed, unaggregated results.

Optional Values:

- Year
- Month
- Day
- All

parameters.name: Dimension
parameters.description:
The dimension names. (Equivalent to SQL's GROUP BY Clause)
Optional Values:

- UserId
- ServiceId
- ServiceVersion
- ServiceInstanceId
- DeploySucceeded
- ErrorType
- ErrorCode

parameters.name: EndTime
parameters.description: The end of the time range to query. The end time must be later than the start time. Specify the time in the ISO 8601 standard in the YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssZ format. The time must be in UTC.

parameters.name: MaxResults
parameters.description: The number of entries per page. Valid values: 1 to 100. Default value: 20.

parameters.name: NextToken
parameters.description: The pagination token that is used in the next request to retrieve a new page of results. You do not need to specify this parameter for the first request. You must specify the token that is obtained from the previous query as the value of NextToken.

parameters.name: StartTime
parameters.description: The beginning of the time range to query. Specify the time in the ISO 8601 standard in the *yyyy-MM-dd*T*HH:mm*Z format. The time must be in UTC.
